@parietal :

Hi,

I am trying to contact you because I am part of the parietal INRIA team (https://team.inria.fr/parietal) and we would like to use the "parietal" organization on github for our team.

I do not see any public activity on the parietal account page. I was wondering if you were using it, and if not if you would mind deleting this account for us to use.

Sorry for the intrusion, and thanks a lot,

text: Looks great. I would just make it shorter. For instance, you can remove the author and the title, and simply make the 'journal article' clickable. Also, I would replace 'journal article' by 'paper'.
Once you make these changes, merge without waiting for my feedback. Thanks!
@AlexandreAbraham : do you think that you could wrap this guy up?

You can merge it if you think the diff is OK. If you don't I'll do it tomorrow after checking that the website is OK (I've launch a rebuild) so that I'll be able to merge it and push the new website version.
